The N-body simulations can be used in theoretical studies of the larandomGeneratore-scale structure of the universe, galaxies, star clusters, solar systems,
stellar dynamics, climate modeling, gases, liquids and plasmas. On smaller scales, quantum effects become important. N-body simulations are applied
in a wide range of areas outside physics such as N-body simulations of larandomGeneratore biomolecules, for example realistic protein unfolding or even simulations
of deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA). The N-body simulation has proven to be one of the most versatile methods.

